        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@mhinz thanks for the tip, but I always can't (or don't) remember where the `*` should be, for example, if there's a file name `gulpfile.prod.js` and what I remember is `prod` I have to type `*prod*` and tab to complete. why should I type `*` if the system could work without that stuff?\r\n\r\nI use fuzzy-finders to find files in deep folders, but they're much inefficient for edit file in current directory, since you have to type command to open the new window, type and filter lots of items and then confirm. I would prefer `:e xxx<tab>` and then `<cr>`",
