            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@ZyX-I Just tried zsh, it works just like vim and other shell, you have to type * when you can't remember the start part of path.\r\n\r\nAnother nice complete feature of fish is it could prompt for complete the latest matched command  just after user type `command` and `<space>` like:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"180\" alt=\"screen shot 2016-12-16 at 9 36 59 pm\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/251450/21264611/090331e8-c3d8-11e6-9089-56e5690910b2.png\">\r\n\r\nI can just type `<tab>` to complete the command.\r\n\r\nYou're the lucky ones who (probably) works with one language at one time, for me (as a front-end developer), a project could contains many folders and each one contains `verylongname.html` `verylongname.css` `verylongname.js` `verylongname.json` and others, it would be great if I can type `:e html` and `<tab>` to complete html files. ",
